<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375696FF23D225FA38FBFD608D" authority="Thomas, 1901" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[798,1098,1498,1522]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="138" pageNumber="138" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65696FF23D225FA38FC1D608E" box="[798,938,1498,1521]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="138">Myotis simus</emphasis>
Thomas, 1901
</taxonomicName>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="354B36B45696FF23D3F7F9E9FCE6631A" blockId="138.[684,1212,1547,1737]" pageId="138" pageNumber="138">VOUCHER MATERIAL (TOTAL = 3): Orosa (AMNH 74105, 74109, 74110); see table 61 for measurements.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7DEE653F5696FF22D3F7F98DFDAE66CF" lastPageId="139" lastPageNumber="139" pageId="138" pageNumber="138" type="description">
<paragraph id="354B36B45696FF23D3F7F98DFBDE63F9" blockId="138.[684,1212,1547,1737]" box="[716,1129,1647,1671]" pageId="138" pageNumber="138">UNVOUCHERED OBSERVATIONS: None.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="354B36B45696FF23D3F7F972FB0B63B6" blockId="138.[684,1212,1547,1737]" pageId="138" pageNumber="138">
IDENTIFICATION: The primary diagnostic characteristic of 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375696FF23D25EF953FC4463B7" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[869,1011,1713,1736]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="138" pageNumber="138" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65696FF23D25EF953FC4463B7" box="[869,1011,1713,1736]" italics="true" pageId="138" pageNumber="138">Myotis simus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is the attachment
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="354B36B45697FF22D157FF00FDE36653" blockId="139.[108,637,226,1010]" pageId="139" pageNumber="139">
of the plagiopatagium at the ankle or at the level of the toes by a narrow (&lt;1.5 mm wide) band of membrane (López-González et al., 2001). Additionally, 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375697FF22D1F3FEA4FE9D6422" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[200,298,326,349]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="139" pageNumber="139" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65697FF22D1F3FEA4FE9D6422" box="[200,298,326,349]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="139">M. simus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has short (&lt;
<quantity id="F20C9B515697FF22D08BFEA7FE436422" box="[432,500,325,349]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="139" pageNumber="139" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
), woolly fur; lacks a fringe of hairs along the trailing edge of the uropatagium; sagittal and lambdoidal crests are present; and the occipital region is flattened posteriorly (Moratelli, 2012). Descriptions and measurements of 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375697FF22D007FE09FE12677D" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[316,421,491,514]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="139" pageNumber="139" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65697FF22D007FE09FE12677D" box="[316,421,491,514]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="139">M. simus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were provided by Miller (1928), Handley (1960), LaVal (1973), Carter and Dolan (1978), López-González et al. (2001), Wilson (2008b), Moratelli (2012), Moratelli et al. (2011a, 2013, 2015b), and Moratelli and Wilson (2014a). No subspecies are currently recognized (Moratelli, 2012), but a revision is needed due to the suspected presence of cryptic molecular diversity within this taxon as currently recognized (Larsen et al., 2012).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="354B36B45697FF22D1B7FCD7FDAE66CF" blockId="139.[108,637,226,1010]" pageId="139" pageNumber="139">
Moratelli et al. (2013) identified the material from Orosa as 
<taxonomicName id="F2F44D375697FF22D02DFCB5FE126611" authorityName="Thomas" authorityYear="1901" box="[278,421,855,878]" class="Mammalia" family="Vespertilionidae" genus="Myotis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Chiroptera" pageId="139" pageNumber="139" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="simus">
<emphasis id="0780EAA65697FF22D02DFCB5FE126611" box="[278,421,855,878]" italics="true" pageId="139" pageNumber="139">Myotis simus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and we agree that these specimens conform to previous descriptions and measurements of the species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="7DEE653F5697FF22D1B7FC5BFDB7668D" pageId="139" pageNumber="139" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="354B36B45697FF22D1B7FC5BFDB7668D" blockId="139.[108,637,226,1010]" pageId="139" pageNumber="139">REMARKS: No ecological information is available about this species in our region.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
